Candles lit all around.

1060
00:49:54,719 --> 00:49:55,759
You look peaceful.

1061
00:50:01,199 --> 00:50:06,960
Maybe these mirrors show a nicer place than being here.

1062
00:50:09,599 --> 00:50:11,279
Uh, what do I see in the mirror?

1063
00:50:12,240 --> 00:50:16,480
Yen Bull, do you walk up to the same mirror or a different mirror?

1064
00:50:16,480 --> 00:50:17,360
Maybe a different one.

1065
00:50:18,160 --> 00:50:21,280
You walk up to one on the opposite side of the hallway

1066
00:50:21,920 --> 00:50:25,120
and you look in and you see an image of yourself

1067
00:50:25,760 --> 00:50:28,720
standing in full armored regalia

1068
00:50:30,720 --> 00:50:35,120
at the face of the entire army of Kalamshan.

1069
00:50:35,119 --> 00:50:41,679
You are calling to them, beckoning to them,

1070
00:50:43,199 --> 00:50:49,039
raising their spirits to fight an unknown enemy on the other side.

1071
00:50:51,440 --> 00:50:55,359
You are leading the country's army

1072
00:50:56,639 --> 00:50:59,440
in what looks like the fight for the country's life.

1073
00:51:00,240 --> 00:51:04,720
Is there another mirror that they haven't looked at yet?

1074
00:51:04,720 --> 00:51:07,039
Uh, the mirrors go all the way down the hall.

1075
00:51:08,159 --> 00:51:08,960
Oh, all right.

1076
00:51:10,639 --> 00:51:11,599
I'll try a new one.

1077
00:51:11,599 --> 00:51:14,559
As you walk past Yen Bull and Thea,

1078
00:51:14,559 --> 00:51:17,920
so we'll say that they're right across from each other, left and right.

1079
00:51:17,920 --> 00:51:21,679
Do I see these same things in their mirrors as I walk by?

1080
00:51:21,679 --> 00:51:24,320
As you walk by, you look into their mirrors.

1081
00:51:25,280 --> 00:51:27,599
In the first one that Thea is looking into,

1082
00:51:28,319 --> 00:51:30,000
you see an image of yourself.

1083
00:51:30,639 --> 00:51:32,799
You're old, older.

1084
00:51:34,639 --> 00:51:37,360
Your beard and hair has grayed completely.

1085
00:51:37,920 --> 00:51:41,599
You're seated at home in an armchair by a fire

1086
00:51:44,480 --> 00:51:45,279
and you're reading.

1087
00:51:48,319 --> 00:51:49,839
Am I reading a story called

1088
00:51:49,839 --> 00:51:52,799
The Wonderful Tale of How Flint Destroyed a Lich?

1089
00:51:54,000 --> 00:51:55,440
Can't quite make out the title.

1090
00:51:57,599 --> 00:52:02,880
In the mirror that Yen Bull is looking into,

1091
00:52:02,880 --> 00:52:05,360
if you kind of look back and forth,

1092
00:52:06,480 --> 00:52:08,960
you see a different image of yourself.

1093
00:52:10,319 --> 00:52:16,079
You see one where you are moving through the woods.

1094
00:52:16,799 --> 00:52:18,319
You're trying to track something.

1095
00:52:19,119 --> 00:52:21,199
You're surrounded by a few others.

1096
00:52:21,839 --> 00:52:23,679
You don't recognize their faces.

1097
00:52:23,680 --> 00:52:28,240
You're following large footprints.

1098
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:32,880
You have on you a bow and arrow and a small hatchet.

1099
00:52:36,640 --> 00:52:38,560
Do you stop at either of those or do you keep walking?

1100
00:52:39,280 --> 00:52:40,400
No, I'm going to keep walking.

1101
00:52:40,400 --> 00:52:41,760
You walk to the next mirror.

1102
00:52:42,480 --> 00:52:45,440
You appear to be back in Mithril Hall.

1103
00:52:46,240 --> 00:52:48,320
You're leaning over a bench.

1104
00:52:50,240 --> 00:52:53,280
You're working hard on something.

1105
00:52:53,280 --> 00:52:56,960
It looks like small metal gears.

1106
00:52:57,600 --> 00:52:58,800
You're putting them together.

1107
00:52:59,920 --> 00:53:03,840
Off in the corner, you see your sister and your father

1108
00:53:05,519 --> 00:53:08,000
working on something very similar.

1109
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:12,080
What do you think these mirrors are showing us?

1110
00:53:13,519 --> 00:53:14,320
I don't know.

1111
00:53:14,320 --> 00:53:21,040
This is me at the head of the army.

1112
00:53:21,039 --> 00:53:23,440
Not...

1113
00:53:23,440 --> 00:53:25,440
Is that something you wish for?

1114
00:53:26,400 --> 00:53:26,639
No.

1115
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:33,199
At this time, at this moment, I would like to fight for my country,

1116
00:53:34,320 --> 00:53:44,159
for my city, but I have never desired to be a leader of the army.

1117
00:53:45,599 --> 00:53:47,759
Yenbul, I assume you turn and address Thea?

1118
00:53:48,800 --> 00:53:49,119
Yeah.

1119
00:53:49,679 --> 00:53:51,519
As you turn, you're looking over her shoulder.

1120
00:53:51,519 --> 00:53:53,279
You see a different image of yourself.

1121
00:53:54,400 --> 00:53:57,679
You're dressed in all black clothing.

1122
00:53:59,119 --> 00:54:00,400
It looks like it's nighttime.

1123
00:54:01,359 --> 00:54:07,039
You and another figure are breaking into a building.

1124
00:54:08,719 --> 00:54:12,719
Silently, you move in and it looks like you're moving

1125
00:54:12,719 --> 00:54:17,279
towards some sort of safe or chest in the back of this room.

1126
00:54:19,119 --> 00:54:27,279
These images keep kind of replaying a specific five or 10 second scene.

1127
00:54:30,079 --> 00:54:31,519
And we can see each other's?

1128
00:54:31,519 --> 00:54:35,440
Like, can I see what Thea is seeing or just my own image of me?

1129
00:54:35,440 --> 00:54:37,279
You only see images of yourself.

1130
00:54:38,000 --> 00:54:38,239
Right.

1131
00:54:40,639 --> 00:54:45,920
I wonder if these are just lies or things that will come to pass

1132
00:54:45,920 --> 00:54:49,280
or things we want.

1133
00:54:51,039 --> 00:54:53,680
Well, here now, I am a thief.

1134
00:54:53,680 --> 00:55:01,599
I'm breaking in to steal something and that is not something that I want or that I would do.

1135
00:55:05,360 --> 00:55:09,440
Maybe they're just meant to distract us and keep us here looking at ourselves.

1136
00:55:10,480 --> 00:55:14,639
Mannix has walked past the three of you and is looking at the mirrors as well,

1137
00:55:14,639 --> 00:55:22,879
and you see them stop on one mirror and they're standing there, like, locked in gaze.

1138
00:55:25,679 --> 00:55:29,920
And they reach up their hand as if trying to move to touch the mirror.

1139
00:55:34,559 --> 00:55:35,920
Mannix, buddy, are you okay?

1140
00:55:37,039 --> 00:55:38,079
Mannix, what do you see?

1141
00:55:40,480 --> 00:55:44,400
I see my daughter.

1142
00:55:44,639 --> 00:55:57,519
Leon, she died years ago, but she's there with me.

1143
00:55:59,279 --> 00:56:01,599
I look different.

1144
00:56:02,239 --> 00:56:04,079
I have long hair.

1145
00:56:09,359 --> 00:56:13,519
I look more like a tracker.

1146
00:56:15,039 --> 00:56:24,559
Maybe these are showing us different lives.

1147
00:56:24,559 --> 00:56:27,839
We could have lived different paths had we chosen differently.

1148
00:56:31,759 --> 00:56:33,759
Do I know anything about special mirrors?

1149
00:56:35,359 --> 00:56:39,359
You know, I used to work in a library in special mirrors.

1150
00:56:39,359 --> 00:56:43,199
Yeah, I've read Harry Potter a lot of times.

1151
00:56:43,280 --> 00:56:44,800
Is this like a mirror of Arasad?

1152
00:56:45,440 --> 00:56:46,240
Just curious.

1153
00:56:48,000 --> 00:56:51,760
No, you don't know specifically anything about these sorts of mirrors.

1154
00:56:53,280 --> 00:56:57,440
How long would you say that you have stood there watching these images roll by?

1155
00:56:58,400 --> 00:57:02,000
I mean, probably not more than 30 seconds for mine.

1156
00:57:02,000 --> 00:57:03,280
It's an old man reading a book.

1157
00:57:03,920 --> 00:57:07,040
Yeah, and if it's only showing, it's like a GIF basically, right?

1158
00:57:07,040 --> 00:57:11,120
It's like showing us like a couple of sections.

1159
00:57:11,120 --> 00:57:11,920
That's fair, yeah.

1160
00:57:13,360 --> 00:57:18,320
Yeah, just no more than I think a couple minutes in total talking about them and looking.

1161
00:57:19,360 --> 00:57:19,600
Yeah.

1162
00:57:21,200 --> 00:57:27,680
You stand there and as you kind of address Mannix, they say,

1163
00:57:30,560 --> 00:57:35,600
It's been so long since I've seen her.

1164
00:57:35,599 --> 00:57:49,199
Here, Leona, my daughter, she died, but here, her face is bright.

1165
00:57:51,599 --> 00:57:55,039
And they reach their hand up and touch the mirror.

1166
00:57:55,039 --> 00:58:07,440
Mannix, I'm sorry, I know what it means to lose a loved one,

1167
00:58:07,440 --> 00:58:13,119
and I can't imagine how you feel seeing them again, but I don't think we can stop here.

1168
00:58:15,360 --> 00:58:19,599
Mannix puts their hand down and looks to you and says,

1169
00:58:21,119 --> 00:58:22,800
What do you mean lost a loved one?

1170
00:58:25,039 --> 00:58:32,719
And as the words leave your lips, there's a switch in your brain.

1171
00:58:34,239 --> 00:58:39,199
Memories flood back of Mannix talking about Leona and going on these adventures

1172
00:58:39,199 --> 00:58:42,079
and going to visit Leona's father.

1173
00:58:42,079 --> 00:58:47,679
You forget why you asked that question.

