Yeah.

1185
00:59:45,519 --> 00:59:46,559
My name is New Lara.

1186
00:59:49,280 --> 00:59:50,800
I was not expecting that.

1187
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:53,920
Well, she had a bit of a moment, panicked.

1188
00:59:54,880 --> 00:59:57,039
She's thinking about New Lara a lot lately, okay?

1189
00:59:57,840 --> 01:00:01,279
Manix speaks up and says, I am Manix.

1190
01:00:02,000 --> 01:00:03,199
Oh, we're giving our real names?

1191
01:00:04,159 --> 01:00:06,880
I mean, saying you're New Lara isn't going to help it.

1192
01:00:06,880 --> 01:00:09,440
New Lara was still a decimator of dragons.

1193
01:00:09,440 --> 01:00:10,480
Shit, well, I didn't know.

1194
01:00:11,279 --> 01:00:12,719
No, you're New Lara now.

1195
01:00:12,719 --> 01:00:17,199
Now, all of this crosstalk has been cut. You are New Lara now. Stick with it.

1196
01:00:17,199 --> 01:00:23,039
Don't get many visitors, but when I do get to show off the fine minutia.

1197
01:00:23,039 --> 01:00:24,000
Nope, gonna sneeze.

1198
01:00:27,119 --> 01:00:28,400
Fuck, it's gone.

1199
01:00:28,400 --> 01:00:28,880
Oh, no.

1200
01:00:31,119 --> 01:00:32,079
Stare into the light.

1201
01:00:32,079 --> 01:00:32,880
Oh, damn it.

1202
01:00:34,079 --> 01:00:36,880
We don't get many visitors, right?

1203
01:00:36,880 --> 01:00:38,559
We don't get many listeners.

1204
01:00:45,599 --> 01:00:49,119
Wallace and the Joy of the Surprises in the Bathroom.

1205
01:00:49,119 --> 01:00:50,880
I see his own spin-off book.

1206
01:00:52,239 --> 01:00:53,279
Sounds like a children's book.

1207
01:00:53,279 --> 01:00:54,000
A little how-to.

1208
01:00:54,000 --> 01:00:57,920
Episode title, Surprises in the Bathroom.

1209
01:00:58,960 --> 01:01:01,440
I also like that Russ prefaced this episode with,

1210
01:01:01,440 --> 01:01:05,039
this is a big episode, and so far we've visited a library in a bathroom.

1211
01:01:06,960 --> 01:01:12,000
It's true. You teed it up pretty big, but we're spending a lot of time in the bathroom.

1212
01:01:12,000 --> 01:01:14,719
Well, this Wallace guy is just such a charmer.

1213
01:01:16,079 --> 01:01:19,039
I want to go and look specifically for, like,

1214
01:01:20,000 --> 01:01:23,840
a biography or perhaps an autobiography of Shang...

1215
01:01:24,639 --> 01:01:25,440
Shangalar.

1216
01:01:25,440 --> 01:01:26,000
Galar.

1217
01:01:26,559 --> 01:01:27,679
Now say it again.

1218
01:01:27,679 --> 01:01:28,719
Shangalar.

1219
01:01:28,719 --> 01:01:30,000
Now say it in sentence.

1220
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:33,679
I would like to go see if there's a biography or autobiography on Shangarlar.

1221
01:01:36,639 --> 01:01:37,519
Shangarlar.

1222
01:01:39,199 --> 01:01:40,000
What is it?

1223
01:01:40,000 --> 01:01:41,440
Shangalar.

1224
01:01:41,440 --> 01:01:45,679
I would like to see if there's an autobiography or biography on Shangalar.

1225
01:01:47,360 --> 01:01:48,239
Yeah, that's good.

1226
01:01:48,240 --> 01:01:49,120
Shangalar.

1227
01:01:49,120 --> 01:01:49,760
Shangalar.

1228
01:01:51,760 --> 01:01:53,040
It's a hard name for me.

1229
01:01:53,680 --> 01:01:56,240
Welcome to the middle. This is actually Amy's Gardening Channel.

1230
01:01:56,960 --> 01:01:59,360
All of your gardening questions are answered here,

1231
01:01:59,360 --> 01:02:03,680
such as the germination rate and when you get to pick your radishes.

1232
01:02:03,680 --> 01:02:04,400
Back to you, Russ.

1233
01:02:05,280 --> 01:02:08,960
Thanks, Amy. Now on the field, we've got Facing Fate.

1234
01:02:10,160 --> 01:02:11,440
Go long, Facing Fate!

1235
01:02:11,440 --> 01:02:12,560
Go long, Facing Fate!

1236
01:02:12,560 --> 01:02:13,600
What is happening?

1237
01:02:15,040 --> 01:02:16,720
I don't know where we are anymore.

1238
01:02:17,280 --> 01:02:19,200
Can someone tell me about Facing Fate?

1239
01:02:19,840 --> 01:02:22,480
Do we feel like this is going well or should we start again?

1240
01:02:22,480 --> 01:02:23,120
No, we're good?

1241
01:02:23,120 --> 01:02:25,040
Yeah, no, this is just for them today.

1242
01:02:25,040 --> 01:02:30,000
I feel like we just need to bring it back to step one where we should have started.

1243
01:02:30,000 --> 01:02:30,640
Okay, cool.

1244
01:02:31,280 --> 01:02:34,880
Hey, we have another show. You may have heard us mention it.

1245
01:02:34,880 --> 01:02:36,560
It's called Facing Fate.

1246
01:02:36,560 --> 01:02:39,760
I feel like I've just turned around a chair and flipped my hat backwards.

1247
01:02:39,760 --> 01:02:43,600
You're going to give some real talk about Facing Fate.

1248
